Barcelona has announced their squad to face Mallorca in tonight’s La Liga clash at the Iberostar Stadium. Barcelona manager, Quique Setién, has named 23 players to face the host in a post on their official website. Setien’s men are currently on top of the La Liga table with two points ahead of Real Madrid. Below is Barcelona squad against Mallorca: Ter Stegen, N. Semedo, Piqué, I. Rakitic, Sergio, Arthur, Suárez, Messi, Neto, Griezmann, Jordi Alba, Braithwaite, S. Roberto, F. De Jong, Vidal, Umtiti, Junior, Iñaki Peña, Riqui Puig, Collado, Ansu Fati, R. Araujo and Monchu. Kick-off time for the match is at 9 pm.